article.headline: Stephen F. Austin 74, Texas A&amp,M-CC 41
article.story: NACOGDOCHES, Texas -- Three players scored 17 points each Saturday and Stephen F. Austin rolled to a 74-41 victory over Texas A&M-Corpus Christi. Antonio Bostic, Taylor Smith and Desmond Haymon led the Lumberjacks (17-11, 10-4 Southland), who shot 61 percent from the field. Smith also grabbed 12 rebounds for Stephen F. Austin, winners of three in a row. Chris Hawkins-Mast had 15 points and 11 rebounds to lead Texas A&M-Corpus Christi. The Islanders (5-23, 3-11), who have two games to play, were officially eliminated from competing in the Southland Conference tournament.
